%N A279200 Number of square permutations of 2n things.
%C A279200 A permutation is said to be square if it can be obtained by shuffling two order-isomorphic patterns.
%H A279200 Samuele Giraudo and Stéphane Vialette, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1601.05962">Unshuffling Permutations</a>, arXiv preprint arXiv:1601.05962 [cs.DS], 2016.
%e A279200 The 20 square permutations of order 4 are 1234, 1243, 1423, 1324, 1342, 4132, 3124, 3142, 3412, 4312, 2134, 2143, 2413, 4213, 2314, 2431, 4231, 3241, 3421, 4321.
%Y A279200 Cf. A191755 (square binary words), A279201, A279202, A279203.
